The course gives an overview of the ethnogenesis of the Baltic nations, the historical development of the languages, the structure and vocabulary of Baltic languages in the Indo-European linguistic environment, language contacts with neighbouring languages, the research history of Baltic languages, the current developments of Lithuanian and Latvian and the language political situation in Lithuania and Latvia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the history of the Baltic nations and languages, the current situation of Lithuanian and Latvian.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the student: a) knows the historical development of the Baltic nations and languages; b) knows the research history of Baltic languages; c) has some knowledge of the distinguishing features of Baltic languages among Indo-European languages; d) has some knowledge of the language contact between Baltic and Balto-Finnic languages; e) knows the situation of Lithuanian and Latvian as official languages.
